body:
Hudson is blue: https://sage.math.washington.edu:8091/hudson/view/cython-mark/

I'd like to merge this in the fusedtypes branch after merge, so that I can then use the utility loader (especially because of the conflicts with the fused function and CyFunction, it's more convenient to work on that in a utility file).

Do you want to review this Dag? Otherwise merging would also be fine. It doesn't have to be thorough and documentation is included.

On 3 September 2011 15:33, vitek
<reply@reply.github.com>
wrote:
>> -    code += dedent("""
>> -        }
>> -
>> -        static void __Pyx_ReleaseBuffer(Py_buffer *view) {
>> -          PyObject* obj = view->obj;
>> -          if (obj) {
>> -            #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x02060000
>> -            if (PyObject_CheckBuffer(obj)) {PyBuffer_Release(view); return;}
>> +    def __init__(self):
>> +        pass
>> +
>> +    def __eq__(self, other):
>> +        return isinstance(other, GetAndReleaseBufferUtilityCode)
>> +
>> +    def __hash__(self):
>> +        return 24342342
>
> What's this?

An implementation of __hash__, it basically makes it a singleton with
respect to how it's added as utility. It could also have been a
global. Anyway, all that the commit does that makes the change is move
it to a utility file.

commit.message: Populate the cython.view module with some Python objects
partial fix of #299.  Refactored buffer auxiliary vars.
Remove hardcoded string, refer to Naming.typeptr_prefix instead.

fixup Revert disturbing the mangling

The extra mangling was needed for closures with identical names, etc.
memoryview utility code pulled in when memview array syntax used in Cython source.
coercion and validation for memoryview wrappers.
consistent naming scheme for memoryviews and memoryview slices.
consistent naming of all memoryview slice and cython.memoryview references.
refactored assignment to memoryviewslice for return values.
moved __Pyx_BufFmt_Context struct definition to proto code in Buffer.py
added array_cwrapper convenience function in CythonScope.py
stubs for MemoryViewSliceType copy() and copy_fortran() functions
updated utility code convenience functions in MemoryView.py
moved memoryview initialization function from CythonUtilCode to pure C
MemoryViewTypeNode -> MemoryViewSliceTypeNode name change in testcase.
set cython.array entry as used when imported.
indexing fix for copy contents C function in MemoryView.py
replacement of 'f' flag with 'fortran' in cython.array.
don't need to calculate itemsize here.
upcase 'access' for memoryviewslice copy code names.
ensure util code isn't declared twice in MemoryViewSliceType
memoryviewslices support in-place copying through to_arr[...] indexing
StructUtilityCode needed a default requires field
replaced memoryviewslice struct diminfo with shape/strides/suboffsets arrays.
needed a check for PyErr_Occurred rather than a check for NULL when calling memview_cwrapper
added .shape .strides and .suboffsets fields to MemoryViewSliceType scope
memoryview fixup and disable one test
Get rid of a lot of entry declarations + optional argument to not allocate buffer in cython.array
Utility Code loader + memview python3 compat
@cname for enum/struct in CythonUtilityCode + simple memslice indexing
Modify utility code loader as per discussion + tests
Move buffer utilities, fix manifest and package data for utilities
Change memview access and packing modifier constants
MemoryViewSlice indexing and object coercion + MemoryView indexing
Acquisition count arguments, attributes + coerce memslice to objects
Memoryview slice item assignment, better errors, pass all tests
Allow contig to follow indirect contig
initializedcheck directive + uninitialized memslice checking + memoryview indexing object<->dtype conversion
memslice decref old item on item assignment
cimport cython in CyUtility, more tests, nogil slicing
Memslice nogil tests, better acquisition counting
Support transposing memoryview objects and slices
Allow C/Fortran contiguity after the last indirect dimension + remove generic_contiguous
Fix incref in test + have_gil arg to xdec_memview on err/return
Support memoryview(slice) -> NumPy coercion + NumPy-like attributes
Support packed struct cython.array cast + better dtype error checking
Bludgeon warning & fix argument unpacking closure leak
Don't merge cython scope into module scope

title: Support for memoryview slices, cython.memoryview, cython.array
